# External Deployment — CONFIRMATION REQUIRED (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

The AI **MAY** execute deployment commands to Kubernetes/OpenShift clusters, but **ONLY after explicit user confirmation**.

## Confirmation Protocol

1. **Show the exact command** that will be executed
2. **Ask for confirmation** — e.g. "Posso executar?"
3. **Wait for explicit YES** from the user
4. Only then execute the command
5. **NEVER batch multiple deploy commands** — confirm each one individually

## Deployment Commands (require confirmation)

- `oc apply` / `oc create` / `oc delete` / `oc rollout restart`
- `helm install` / `helm upgrade` / `helm uninstall`
- `./deploy.sh` / `./cleanup.sh` / `./build-and-push.sh`
- `make deploy-*` / `make infra-install` / `make infra-uninstall`
- `podman push` / `podman build` for images pushed to remote registries
- Any command that modifies a running Kubernetes/OpenShift cluster

## FORBIDDEN Actions (System-Level) — NEVER, even with confirmation

- Starting/stopping Podman machine (`podman machine start/stop`)
- Any command that changes the state of the local virtualization layer

## ALLOWED Actions (no confirmation needed)

- Read cluster state (`oc get`, `oc describe`, `oc logs`)
- Verify code compiles (`mvn clean package -DskipTests`)
- Create/edit scripts, Makefiles, YAML files
- Run local `podman compose up/down` for dev tools
- Run `make sonar-full`, `make sonar-analyze` and similar local analysis tasks
- Run local Testcontainers-based integration tests
